adjectives.description: expectable (comparative more expectable, superlative most expectable)

entries.meaning: Able to be expected or anticipated; not unusual.
examples: Expectable losses are calculated into the final selling price.

entries.meaning: Able to be expected or considered due or required (of someone), reasonable to expect (someone to do, have, etc).
examples: The jury could and did find that appellant's decision not to move was not a decision expectable of a reasonably prudent man to whom any backing vehicle means grave danger.
